00:33:50.770 --> 00:33:55.620
and expand it, I get
divergence is 1 over x squared.

00:33:55.620 --> 00:33:57.810
So you would say how
can you expand it.

00:33:57.810 --> 00:33:59.040
Let's see what happens.

00:33:59.040 --> 00:34:00.100
Let's just do it.

00:34:00.100 --> 00:34:03.611
Let's say we are interested
around lambda or x equals 0.

00:34:08.159 --> 00:34:11.139
We have some
divergencies now, but we

00:34:11.139 --> 00:34:14.630
have to find a way
to deal with it.

00:34:14.630 --> 00:34:17.929
So we get rid of some
of the divergencies

00:34:17.929 --> 00:34:19.780
in the following way.

00:34:19.780 --> 00:34:23.540
By saying, well, if you simply
calculate the zero point

00:34:23.540 --> 00:34:26.090
energy between those
two capacitor plates,

00:34:26.090 --> 00:34:28.570
and then when,
let's say, if there

00:34:28.570 --> 00:34:35.909
is-- if the plates come closer
and there is less zero point

00:34:35.909 --> 00:34:38.989
energy, we would see the
plates attract each other.

00:34:38.989 --> 00:34:42.179
But what happens is the
plates are not moving,

00:34:42.179 --> 00:34:44.690
and there is no
world behind them.

00:34:44.690 --> 00:34:48.250
The world is sort of as it is.

00:34:48.250 --> 00:34:50.520
And that means we
have to sort of now

00:34:50.520 --> 00:34:54.239
look more carefully at the zero
point energy of our capacitor

00:34:54.239 --> 00:34:56.050
plates where l is small.

00:34:56.050 --> 00:34:57.900
And the rest of the world.

00:34:57.900 --> 00:35:01.460
So we are now
representing the world

00:35:01.460 --> 00:35:04.440
as a big capacitor of size l 0.

00:35:04.440 --> 00:35:06.390
And then our plate
is just moving

00:35:06.390 --> 00:35:10.900
within that, because we are
not assuming that then the two

00:35:10.900 --> 00:35:12.830
capacitor plates
attract each other

00:35:12.830 --> 00:35:15.995
and move towards each other
that the size of the universe

00:35:15.995 --> 00:35:17.430
is changing.

00:35:17.430 --> 00:35:21.620
So we want to move a boundary
condition within the universe.

00:35:21.620 --> 00:35:25.240
So therefore, the correct
expression for the zero point

00:35:25.240 --> 00:35:28.940
energy is not the zero
point energy of capacitor l.

00:35:28.940 --> 00:35:31.440
It's the zero point
energy of a capacitor size

00:35:31.440 --> 00:35:35.210
l plus of a capacitor
l0 naught minus l.

00:35:38.240 --> 00:35:41.680
And so we take the
result and simply add

00:35:41.680 --> 00:35:46.340
the expressions for
l and l0 minus l.

00:35:46.340 --> 00:35:51.450
And what is now a nice is that
the first highly divergent term

00:35:51.450 --> 00:35:54.560
with 1 over lambda
to the 4-- reminder

00:35:54.560 --> 00:35:56.810
that we want to let
lambda go to zero.

00:35:56.810 --> 00:35:59.810
It becomes independent of l.

00:35:59.810 --> 00:36:02.700
So we would say, well,
if there is an infinity,

00:36:02.700 --> 00:36:04.700
it doesn't change with l.

00:36:04.700 --> 00:36:06.480
It doesn't provide a potential.

00:36:06.480 --> 00:36:11.130
It's just one of those
infinities which is constant,

00:36:11.130 --> 00:36:13.220
which is not
affecting the physics.

00:36:13.220 --> 00:36:17.940
Also here, this is
independent of l.

00:36:17.940 --> 00:36:24.670
And then the next term gives us
the famous Casimir potential,

00:36:24.670 --> 00:36:28.820
1 over l cubed, and it
is independent of lambda.

00:36:28.820 --> 00:36:31.585
So we have the result which
was independent of the cut

00:36:31.585 --> 00:36:33.020
off we introduced earlier.

00:36:35.570 --> 00:36:40.070
So therefore, we have
derived, with a little bit

00:36:40.070 --> 00:36:43.130
of hand waving to
navigate about infinities,

00:36:43.130 --> 00:36:50.290
that the potential between two
metal plates is 1 over l cubed.

00:36:50.290 --> 00:36:55.130
a squared was the area, the
size of the capacitor plates.

00:36:55.130 --> 00:36:56.560
And this is the exact prefector.

00:36:59.250 --> 00:37:01.690
Or if you want to
figure out what

00:37:01.690 --> 00:37:03.820
is the pressure off the vacuum.

00:37:03.820 --> 00:37:07.007
Pressure is, of course,
force per unit area.

00:37:07.007 --> 00:37:09.090
So you take the derivative
of the potential that's

00:37:09.090 --> 00:37:11.990
the force, that's the
force per unit area,

00:37:11.990 --> 00:37:14.250
and this is now the
vacuum pressure.

00:37:16.800 --> 00:37:18.730
Sort of funny now you
can put in the unit.

00:37:18.730 --> 00:37:21.971
It's 10 to the minus 5
millibar at a distance

00:37:21.971 --> 00:37:22.720
of one micrometer.

00:37:26.530 --> 00:37:30.740
So anyway this is, I think,
the classic deviation

00:37:30.740 --> 00:37:36.100
of the Casimir potential
by, I would say,

00:37:36.100 --> 00:37:38.990
exactly summing
up the zero point

00:37:38.990 --> 00:37:42.210
energy within a certain
boundary condition.

00:37:48.161 --> 00:37:48.660
Good.

00:37:56.570 --> 00:38:00.140
Maybe to address
