for the zero point energy,

00:41:23.260 --> 00:41:25.560
that the zero point
energy is sort of not just

00:41:25.560 --> 00:41:29.450
convenient counting, but
that it is real energy.

00:41:29.450 --> 00:41:32.420
And the Casimir
force, of course, also

00:41:32.420 --> 00:41:35.550
it has often been quoted
as a counter example

00:41:35.550 --> 00:41:37.400
that this is a
direct observation,

00:41:37.400 --> 00:41:39.650
is not-- should not
be regarded as such.

00:41:43.510 --> 00:41:48.850
Now people at MIT
probably know Bob Jaffe.

00:41:48.850 --> 00:41:51.560
He's a high energy physicist.

00:41:51.560 --> 00:41:54.310
And why is he interested
in atomic physics?

00:41:54.310 --> 00:41:57.015
Why is he interested
in the Casimir force?

00:41:57.015 --> 00:42:00.680
Well, the question of
zero point energies

00:42:00.680 --> 00:42:05.060
is very, very important in
these days for dark energy.

00:42:05.060 --> 00:42:08.550
I mean, you know that 80% of
the energy of the universe

00:42:08.550 --> 00:42:11.200
is dark energy.

00:42:11.200 --> 00:42:13.930
Then there's dark matter, and
then there is baryonic matter.

00:42:13.930 --> 00:42:16.690
But this dark energy
is really mysterious.

00:42:16.690 --> 00:42:18.810
And one candidate
for dark energy

00:42:18.810 --> 00:42:23.062
is the dark energy simply comes
from the zero point energy.

00:42:23.062 --> 00:42:24.520
So therefore, people
are now really

00:42:24.520 --> 00:42:27.280
interested is the
dark energy real.

00:42:27.280 --> 00:42:31.380
And if it is real, does it
have a gravitational effect?

00:42:31.380 --> 00:42:33.320
Does it change the
metric of space?

00:42:33.320 --> 00:42:35.955
And can it accelerate the
expansion of the universe?

00:42:42.820 --> 00:42:46.140
Of course, you have a problem
if you calculate the zero point

00:42:46.140 --> 00:42:48.530
energy, you don't
introduce a cut off.

00:42:48.530 --> 00:42:52.230
You have a spectacular
uv divergence.

00:42:52.230 --> 00:42:57.590
You can maybe now
concatenate the divergence

00:42:57.590 --> 00:43:03.570
by saying, OK, eventually if
the wavelengths become shorter

00:43:03.570 --> 00:43:06.120
and shorter and shorter,
there is a cut off.

00:43:06.120 --> 00:43:09.740
And if you have no
idea at all, you

00:43:09.740 --> 00:43:12.000
would introduce a cut off
at the Planck lengths,

00:43:12.000 --> 00:43:14.770
because beyond
the Planck lengths

00:43:14.770 --> 00:43:17.280
all physical
descriptions break down.

00:43:17.280 --> 00:43:19.870
But if you cut it off
at the Planck lengths,

00:43:19.870 --> 00:43:23.520
you find that the zero
point energy of all modes

00:43:23.520 --> 00:43:28.570
is larger than the observed
dark energy in the universe

00:43:28.570 --> 00:43:31.060
for acceleration of
the cosmic expansion

00:43:31.060 --> 00:43:34.970
by 124 orders of magnitude.

00:43:34.970 --> 00:43:37.920
And if you think you want
to introduce a cut off which

00:43:37.920 --> 00:43:41.340
is maybe the classical
electron radius.

00:43:41.340 --> 00:43:43.540
The classical electron
radius is the radius

00:43:43.540 --> 00:43:47.980
of a charged sphere for which
the electrostatic energy would

00:43:47.980 --> 00:43:51.590
just be the rest
energy of the electron.

00:43:51.590 --> 00:43:55.310
Well, then you're off by
43 orders of magnitude.

00:43:55.310 --> 00:43:57.940
So some people have called
those discrepancies,

00:43:57.940 --> 00:44:00.960
which are completely
unresolved as of now,

00:44:00.960 --> 00:44:05.490
the biggest failure ever
of theoretical physics.

00:44:05.490 --> 00:44:09.410
So anyway, that's why there is
renewed interest in the Casimir

00:44:09.410 --> 00:44:10.180
force.

00:44:10.180 --> 00:44:13.140
And at least in
electromagnetics,

00:44:13.140 --> 00:44:14.940
we have a very,
very simple model.

00:44:14.940 --> 00:44:17.450
And we have experiments which
measure the Casimir force,

00:44:17.450 --> 00:44:22.010
but, as I've said, it cannot
be regarded as a direct

00:44:22.010 --> 00:44:24.017
observation of the
zero point energy.

00:44:27.840 --> 00:44:32.230
