00:57:55.190 --> 00:57:58.240
of atoms with resonant
light, because this

00:57:58.240 --> 00:58:01.070
is when we have divergencies.

00:58:01.070 --> 00:58:03.730
If we have state a, state b.

00:58:03.730 --> 00:58:07.760
We have a laser and
we scatter light.

00:58:07.760 --> 00:58:18.190
If the frequency is
approximately resonant,

00:58:18.190 --> 00:58:27.960
then those perturbative
results have a divergency.

00:58:27.960 --> 00:58:32.000
So for resonant light
scattering, the typical matrix

00:58:32.000 --> 00:58:35.410
element we are interested in,
we start and end of course

00:58:35.410 --> 00:58:36.370
in the ground state.

00:58:36.370 --> 00:58:37.300
We scatter photon.

00:58:37.300 --> 00:58:41.110
We go up to an excited state
and go back to the ground state.

00:58:41.110 --> 00:58:45.410
But we started initially with
a photon of wave vector k

00:58:45.410 --> 00:58:48.060
and polarization epsilon.

00:58:48.060 --> 00:58:50.270
And this may be different
for the scattered light.

00:58:54.720 --> 00:59:04.780
The interaction happens by
the interaction operator,

00:59:04.780 --> 00:59:09.950
which, for the purpose
of this discussion,

00:59:09.950 --> 00:59:15.480
can either be the A dot p
term or the d dot E term.

00:59:15.480 --> 00:59:17.230
We've discussed about
the special role

00:59:17.230 --> 00:59:18.730
of the a squared term.

00:59:18.730 --> 00:59:20.180
We discussed it earlier.

00:59:20.180 --> 00:59:23.090
I don't want to include it
in the discussion right now.

00:59:28.400 --> 00:59:33.395
And then you would
say-- just want

00:59:33.395 --> 00:59:34.770
to make sure they
do not confuse.

00:59:34.770 --> 00:59:36.610
In second order
perturbation theory,

00:59:36.610 --> 00:59:39.230
you always have an
energy denominator.

00:59:39.230 --> 00:59:42.110
But as I also explained to
you, the energy denominator

00:59:42.110 --> 00:59:45.340
comes from the free propagator.

00:59:45.340 --> 00:59:48.010
You had a dot
propagate and a dot--

00:59:48.010 --> 00:59:52.030
and what is the time evolution
of this free propagation when

00:59:52.030 --> 00:59:53.580
you integrate it with time?

00:59:53.580 --> 00:59:55.500
This gave rise to the
energy denominator.

00:59:55.500 --> 00:59:56.547
Just a side remark.

00:59:56.547 --> 00:59:58.130
So you should be
very familiar that we

00:59:58.130 --> 00:59:59.830
have an energy denominator.

00:59:59.830 --> 01:00:03.260
But now this energy
denominator--

01:00:03.260 --> 01:00:06.570
the initial energy is
the initial atomic state

01:00:06.570 --> 01:00:09.570
plus the photon.

01:00:09.570 --> 01:00:13.360
And then if you want
to sum over all states,

01:00:13.360 --> 01:00:17.090
I can just put in
here the operator H0.

01:00:17.090 --> 01:00:20.110
But you may immediately think
about it, the only state which

01:00:20.110 --> 01:00:23.570
really matters is the state b.

01:00:23.570 --> 01:00:28.450
And what matters is only when
we go through intermediate state

01:00:28.450 --> 01:00:32.860
b, then H0 is Eb, and
then we have a divergence

01:00:32.860 --> 01:00:34.720
because the denominator is 0.

01:00:37.240 --> 01:00:41.380
So let's see how we can fix it.

01:00:41.380 --> 01:00:44.250
But let me first give you
the perturbative result,

01:00:44.250 --> 01:00:49.040
which you have seen
many, many times.

01:00:49.040 --> 01:00:54.020
It is the product of
two matrix elements.

01:00:54.020 --> 01:00:56.580
We have an intermediate state.

01:00:56.580 --> 01:00:59.720
The excited state
without photon.

01:00:59.720 --> 01:01:06.880
We started with a photon,
and we end up with a photon.

01:01:06.880 --> 01:01:12.770
And here we have our
dipole or A dot p term.

01:01:12.770 --> 01:01:20.170
And our energy
denominator diverges

01:01:20.170 --> 01:01:24.890
when the frequency of the
photon approaches the resonance

01:01:24.890 --> 01:01:25.390
frequency.

01:01:28.410 --> 01:01:32.260
Well, how can we fix it?

01:01:32.260 --> 01:01:37.150
You know that in
many cases you're

01:01:37.150 --> 01:01:43.100
just adding an
imaginary part to it,

01:01:43.100 --> 01:01:48.480
which reflects that, due to
the coupling with the vacuum

01:01:48.480 --> 01:01:52.590
of the electromagnetic field,
the excited state is broadened.

01:01:52.590 --> 01:01:56.460
And it gives its energy
an imaginary part.

01:01:56.460 --> 01:01:59.240
This of course is
very phenomenological,

01:01:59.240 --> 01:02:07.580
but at least technically
it avoids the divergence.

01:02:07.580 --> 01:02:13.070
Now what I want to show
you, in the next 15 minutes

01:02:13.070 --> 01:02:17.320
and we continue on
