01:02:17.320 --> 01:02:21.060
I can get this result of
a very rigorous approach.

01:02:21.060 --> 01:02:22.900
I want to use the
diagrammatic approach.

01:02:22.900 --> 01:02:25.510
I want to sum an infinite
number of diagrams.

01:02:25.510 --> 01:02:30.680
And will tell you what are the
approximations to get this.

01:02:30.680 --> 01:02:35.880
For instance, as you know, when
you have an imaginary part,

01:02:35.880 --> 01:02:38.460
when you have just an
imaginary part of the energy,

01:02:38.460 --> 01:02:41.940
the physics of it is
exponential decay.

01:02:41.940 --> 01:02:45.040
Well I hope, not today
but on Wednesday,

01:02:45.040 --> 01:02:50.360
you realize what assumptions
lead to exponential decay,

01:02:50.360 --> 01:02:54.350
and that, in principle, non
