01:02:54.350 --> 01:02:57.810
the standard than the exception.

01:02:57.810 --> 01:02:59.870
But the effects are small.

01:02:59.870 --> 01:03:01.700
But I want to show you.

01:03:01.700 --> 01:03:05.130
So in some sense
I want to give--

01:03:05.130 --> 01:03:07.200
we have to go through
a half an hour of work

01:03:07.200 --> 01:03:08.770
to derive this result.

01:03:08.770 --> 01:03:10.210
So you'd say, what's about it?

01:03:10.210 --> 01:03:11.930
You just get the
phenomenological result.

01:03:11.930 --> 01:03:15.870
Well, we have put it
on a rigorous basis.

01:03:15.870 --> 01:03:19.630
And number two is we do
understand what assumptions

01:03:19.630 --> 01:03:22.050
really go into this
phenomenological result.

01:03:25.490 --> 01:03:31.680
So the way how we will
actually obtain this result

01:03:31.680 --> 01:03:49.510
is that in-- the second order
diagram is that you start

01:03:49.510 --> 01:03:52.980
in state a, you go in state
b, and you're back in state a,

01:03:52.980 --> 01:03:56.190
and you exchange photons.

01:03:56.190 --> 01:04:03.650
So the way how we-- the physical
picture we want to use now

01:04:03.650 --> 01:04:12.540
is after the photon is
absorbed right here,

01:04:12.540 --> 01:04:18.855
the system is not propagating
with the Hamiltonian H0.

01:04:18.855 --> 01:04:24.220
It will propagate with
the Hamiltonian H.

01:04:24.220 --> 01:04:29.010
If we do that, then we
avoid the divergence.

01:04:29.010 --> 01:04:32.230
We get a result which can be
applied toward-- the formalism

01:04:32.230 --> 01:04:34.080
can be applied to
many situations.

01:04:34.080 --> 01:04:37.910
And in one limiting
case, we obtain that.

01:04:37.910 --> 01:04:41.840
So the physics behind
it is the following.

01:04:41.840 --> 01:04:45.260
The divergence which we
encounter in resonant physics

01:04:45.260 --> 01:04:50.705
is only a divergence because
we assume the atom in state b

01:04:50.705 --> 01:04:52.210
is naked.

01:04:52.210 --> 01:04:55.530
It's an excited state
of an isolated atom.

01:04:55.530 --> 01:04:59.290
But in reality, the
state b interacts

01:04:59.290 --> 01:05:01.530
by virtual photon
emission, interacts

01:05:01.530 --> 01:05:03.900
with all the modes
of the vacuum.

01:05:03.900 --> 01:05:08.320
And once we throw that in
by saying that between two--

01:05:08.320 --> 01:05:10.640
between absorbing and
emitting a photon,

01:05:10.640 --> 01:05:14.630
the state b propagates not
with a free Hamiltonian,

01:05:14.630 --> 01:05:19.640
but with the total Hamiltonian,
we avoid the divergence.

01:05:19.640 --> 01:05:22.910
But this is no longer
a perturbative result.

01:05:22.910 --> 01:05:26.820
And let me illustrate
that to you.

01:05:30.580 --> 01:05:38.590
If you take the energy
denominator, omega minus

01:05:38.590 --> 01:05:47.980
and omega 0, and we add
the imaginary part to it,

01:05:47.980 --> 01:06:00.560
I can Taylor expand it, assuming
the imaginary part is small.

01:06:06.970 --> 01:06:10.220
Well, that's sort of
a trivial expansion,

01:06:10.220 --> 01:06:13.210
but now you should
know that gamma,

01:06:13.210 --> 01:06:15.400
the rate of
spontaneous emission,

01:06:15.400 --> 01:06:17.990
the simplest
expression is obtained

01:06:17.990 --> 01:06:20.470
in [INAUDIBLE] is called
null in the second order

01:06:20.470 --> 01:06:23.450
in the interaction Hamiltonian.

01:06:23.450 --> 01:06:25.310
Spontaneous emission
is proportional

01:06:25.310 --> 01:06:28.370
to the atomic dipole
matrix element squared.

01:06:28.370 --> 01:06:30.840
So it's second order
in the Hamiltonian.

01:06:30.840 --> 01:06:35.525
But that means that
this harmless addition

01:06:35.525 --> 01:06:40.230
of an imaginary part means
that if you look at the Taylor

01:06:40.230 --> 01:06:45.590
expansion, that we are
using now infinite orders.

01:06:45.590 --> 01:06:47.835
Infinite orders
in this expansion.

01:07:00.370 --> 01:07:07.070
So the phenomenological
addition of [INAUDIBLE] gamma

01:07:07.070 --> 01:07:10.980
to the excited level b is
actually highly nontrivial,

01:07:10.980 --> 01:07:13.290
because it's
corresponds technically

01:07:13.290 --> 01:07:17.600
or physically to a non
perturbative result which

01:07:17.600 --> 01:07:21.455
involves infinite order in the
interaction matrix element.

